annotationA: Sec61 alpha subunit is a subunit of the the translocon, a protein-conducting channel that mediates the co-translational transport of nascent polypeptides into the endoplasmic reticulum. Sec61 alpha is a subunit of the Sec61 heterotrimer that forms the core of translocon channel
annotationB: Secretory 23, isoform E; GTPase activator activity; zinc ion binding; Sar GTPase activator activity
